The paper proposes a method for efficiently computing distances using low memory, which is a common problem in many areas of computer science. The method involves statistical estimation and has applications in large-scale learning tasks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.IT (information theory), cs.NA (numerical analysis), and cs.SI (social and information networks).
